SIMPLE: brinksmanship
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: brinksmanship
<hw>brinks"man*ship</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>brink</ets> + <ets>-manship</ets>.
(1956).]</ety> <def>the policy or practise of pushing a dangerous
situation to the brink of disaster (to the limits of safety), in order
to achieve the most advantageous outcome; -- used especially of
diplomatic maneuvers in crisis situations, and originally applied to the
policies of <person>John Foster Dulles</person> under President
Eisenhower.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Briny</ent>⟦br⟧
